HEADWORD: Milreis
<hw>Mil"reis`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pg. <ets>mil
reis</ets>, i. e., one thousand reis; <ets>mil</ets> a thousand +
<ets>reis</ets>, pl. of <ets>real</ets> a rei.]</ety> <def>A Portuguese
money of account rated in the treasury department of the United States
at one dollar and eight cents; also, a Brazilian money of account rated
at fifty-four cents and six mills (1913).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

